Software
===========
Required packages:
Python 2.7
numpy
-Download from http://sourceforge.net/projects/numpy/files/NumPy/
pyaudio
-Download from http://people.csail.mit.edu/hubert/pyaudio/
PySerial
-Download from http://pypi.python.org/pypi/pyserial
Python Image Library
-Download from http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/


GE Lights
===========
Windows:
Plug in the Arduino UNO USB device, wait for the driver software installation to fail
Open Device Manager in Control Panel, right click on the "Arduino UNO" device
Select "Update driver software"
Choose the driver location manually, and select the Drivers folder in this directory
The installation should finish, and your Device Manager should now have an entry called "Communications Port (COM4)" in Ports. Note that you may see a number other than 4. 

